New Records: Harry Kane marked his 100th England cap with a double to see off Finland
Key Match Events: Harry Kane scored with a powerful shot to break the deadlock
Noni Madueke pulled back; Kane banged first time into the far corner for his second goal
Pre-Game Insights: Harry Kane wanted 100 England goals, which sounded like wishful thinking
Harry Kane was central to virtually everything in the first half but the breakthrough eluded him
Post-Match Reflections: Lee Carsley praised Harry Kane and said it was a huge win for the team
Kane's family in the stands received heartfelt applause when he was withdrawn
Miscellaneous Highlights: Trent Alexander-Arnold had a sumptuous passing display and was instrumental in creating scoring opportunities
Angel Gomes made his full debut and had a deep-lying central midfield role, moving it briskly and smartly
Others: England interim manager Lee Carsley emphasized the importance of control and fluidity in the team's play
